                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The tents to the right of zone in is where you want to pull from. The technique I have used through many many camps is to have a puller run up and aggro the named human mob you want to kill. Then the puller trains that mob plus any adds to ZO. Once the puller zones, anyone in the group can hail the mob (or mobs) you want to kill and they will stand there till all their buddies have wandered off back to the tents. Once the puller is back in, go ahead and kill.
<br />

<br />
These guys do hit hard and fast, so make sure you got a good tank (8k+ preferred) and damn good healer (s). They tend to surprise you with a triple or quad and drop a tank from half to almost dead real fast. The models in the fancy white armor are prime targets and are more likely to not be mezzable. The other named in the normal armor almost all are mezzable (seem to recall having one immune once). I have managed 2 or 3 while the group is on one but we tend to keep it safe with just one extra mob lined up.
<br />

<br />
The big building immediately to the right of ZI has 2 mobs at the top of the steps in the white armor model. These are good for Sacred Water, also. Beware the short one. If he pops, make sure you kill him first.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
