                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You can do the whole thing solo, not very hard but it is annoying.
<br />

<br />
There is a worm thingy right next the the PoT stone, tash/charm/haste. Using pacification split the 2 guards in the house. Root the pull, slow it and sic the pet (pet can't handle these mobs unlsowed). Drop a couple of nukes. If (more when) root breaks DON'T re-root it. Once dead - loot and zone. If charm breaks don't think about recharming unless you can handle some major damage (pet has to re-gain aggro), just zone.
<br />

<br />
Zone back in and your pet is now at 100% hp - wow! (remember to refresh tash every 6-7 minutes, or 2 zonings.) Its also non-KoS.
<br />

<br />
To split the named in the tents is easy, must have run3-5 or SoW though. Run in to the camp and target a suit. Run out and at max range hit it with tash. Run back to the zone out and wait. When the mobs get close hammer that mouse button and zone. Zone back in (this is where SoW is handy), run over the hill and start hailing the named - with any luck at least 1 of them is still around. The named will stand and talk to you whilst everyone else paths back to the camp.
<br />
Root, (tash)Slow named and charm wormy, rinse repeat.
<br />

<br />
Now, there are 2 tricks to this place.
<br />

<br />
1) The Named (suits) summon. If you have rooted them a "safe" distance from the exit you will never make it, as you will get bounced. If they are not rooted however - they run after you and you get closer all the time. This is why you don't recast root after your pet gets aggro.
<br />

<br />
2) One of the house suits can spawn as a mini-me. This git is evil. No slow, no root and its a yellow con so no paci. Load up your 2 nukes and kite in a tight circle until your pet has aggro - then chain nuke. Hope charm doesn't break. Hope pet doesn't die.
<br />

<br />
Its not particually fun way of getting the water but it saves finding a group and it can get rather exciting <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Disclaimer: It is your problem, not mine, when you die.</span></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
